Product Meaning of Wave 1

Wave 1 answered a very practical product problem:

how can TraceFold become easier to use every day without changing what the system fundamentally is?

It did so by making:

single-item input lighter
larger-volume intake more practical
upstream capture handling more triage-friendly
detail pages easier to scan and compare across domains

Wave 1 therefore made TraceFold feel more usable in repeated daily work, but still primarily within the existing Web-centered surface model.

Phase 3 Wave 2 — Closed Scope

Phase 3 Wave 2, in its currently closed bounded form, is the Lightweight Capture Adapters Pack.

This pack includes:

Unified adapter contract baseline
Telegram bot V1
Telegram acceptance / hardening
Feishu bot V1
Feishu acceptance / hardening
TG / Feishu cross-platform closure
A. Adapter contract baseline

This baseline established that lightweight adapters must remain:

text-only in first version
one message -> one capture
capture-first
structure-later
review-later
light success/failure acknowledgement
no direct-to-formal path
no Pending bypass
no review actions
no AI behavior
no workflow/control-surface drift

This was essential to prevent adapter drift into independent product lines.

B. Telegram adapter baseline

Telegram was formalized as:

a lightweight text-to-capture adapter
minimal /start and /help
light success/failure acknowledgement
source traceability aligned with contract
no broader bot-surface drift

Telegram then received bounded acceptance/hardening around:

runtime/startup clarity
setup guide alignment
contract inheritance verification
source metadata verification
C. Feishu adapter baseline

Feishu was formalized as:

a lightweight text-to-capture adapter
webhook-based message-to-capture path
minimal help/usage behavior
light success/failure acknowledgement
source traceability aligned with contract
no workflow / review / approval-bot drift

Feishu then received bounded acceptance/hardening around:

webhook/runtime clarity
URL verification behavior
setup/config clarity
contract inheritance verification
source metadata verification
D. Cross-platform adapter closure

Telegram and Feishu were then reviewed together and confirmed to be:

true contract siblings
semantically parallel
similarly bounded in product scope
sufficiently mature to close together as one bounded lightweight adapter pack

This closure does not claim a bot platform.
It claims only a bounded lightweight adapter pack.

Product Meaning of Wave 2

Wave 2 answered the next natural product question after Wave 1:

once Web-side intake is smoother, how can recording begin more naturally from message-based environments without creating new business centers?

Wave 2’s significance is that TraceFold now supports lower-friction entry not only inside Web, but also from bounded external chat-like surfaces.

This matters because it extends the rhythm of use:

not just “open the workbench and then record”
but also “start recording naturally where you already are”

And it does so without abandoning:

capture-first semantics
one business-logic center
one main chain
Web as the main business interface
How Wave 1 and Wave 2 Relate

Wave 1 and Wave 2 are not separate themes by accident.
They are two layers of the same broader Phase 3 logic.

Wave 1

Improved daily-use intake and readback inside the main workbench surfaces.

Wave 2

Extended low-friction intake outside the main workbench surfaces, but only through bounded adapters that still feed the same chain.

This means Phase 3 so far is coherent:

Wave 1 improved internal daily-use usability
Wave 2 improved external low-friction entry
neither wave changed the architecture center
neither wave created a new product center

Together they form a believable Phase 3 progression rather than a bag of unrelated work.

