Reasonable Next-Step Directions After Wave 2

This summary does not choose the next wave, but it clarifies what kinds of next steps are now reasonable.

Possible next directions include:

1. Further daily-use hardening

A future bounded pack could continue improving stability, operability, or cumulative daily-use smoothness.

2. Read/list consistency extension

A future bounded pack could extend current detail/readback consistency logic into broader list-level consistency and readback continuity.

3. Adapter usability extension

A future bounded pack could improve adapter ergonomics, operations, or setup quality without changing their role.

4. Broader Phase 3 re-evaluation

If enough usage evidence accumulates, it may become appropriate to define a new Phase 3 wave with a clearer next theme.

What should not happen is silently appending unrelated work into already-closed bounded packs.

Recommended Post-Summary Rule

After this summary, no additional work should be silently folded back into:

Phase 3 Wave 1 Input-side pack
Phase 3 Wave 1 Readback / Detail Density pack
Phase 3 Wave 2 Lightweight Capture Adapters pack

Any further work should be opened as a new explicitly scoped pack or wave.

That keeps the closure history trustworthy and makes future planning clearer.

